The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ICC hauls up Hill 
                                                                                                                       7                                      ICC hauls up Hill 
                      
	Wellington: The International Cricket Council (ICC) has reprimanded New Zealand umpire Tony Hill for publicly stating that he suspected the no balls bowled by the Pakistani pacers  Mohammed Asif and Mohammed Aamer  during the Lords Test in England to be deliberate, according to a report.         
	According to a report, the ICC has reprimanded Hill for talking publicly about the betting scam surrounding the England-Pakistan Test at Lords.         
	ICC has told him not to comment further until the investigation into the matter has been completed, the report claimed.           (REUTERS)                                                                                                                 
